news_header: The Helsinki Stock Exchange Superweek is active with 30 companies reporting results tomorrow. Today, 15 companies announced their performance, including Cargotec and Anora. The general index rose by 0.7%. Kempower saw a significant increase of 14.2% in its share price after strong order intake. Anora's profitability improved despite a decrease in turnover.
news_original_title: Tulosjulkistajat Kempower ja Anora kiitävät pörssin nousuavauksessa
news_text: Other notable performers include Noho Partners and Remedy, while Cargotec and Kyawise faced challenges. Springfield plans to propose a higher dividend compared to last year.
